  "text": "Cells-CDH17 overexpression has been reported in some pancreatic tumors [CITATION_1] . Here, in a sample set of 48 patients with pancreatic cancer, we detected CDH17 expression in 60.4% of tumors by immunohistochemistry. Among CDH17-positive tumors, 62.1% showed intense staining, indicating overexpression of CDH17 (Fig. 8A ). To learn whether our findings could be extended to pancreatic cancer, we used the BxPC3, PANC-1, and CAPAN pancreatic cancer cell lines. PANC-1 and CAPAN cells showed expression of CDH17, but BxPC3 did not (Fig. 8B ). After transfection with CDH17-WT and CDH17-RAD mutant vectors, we observed clear differences in adhesion capacity. Although CDH17-WT caused a clear increase in the three cell lines, the RAD mutant failed to increase adhesion above basal levels (Fig. 8C ). Moreover, cell proliferation increased in CDH17-RGD transfectants but not in cells transfected with CDH17-RAD (Fig. 8D) . These results support an extension of our findings to other cancers expressing CDH17, like pancreatic cancer. ",
